HEADWORD: Flare-up
<hw>Flare"-up`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
sudden burst of anger or passion; an angry dispute.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sudden bursting into flame; a flaring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flaring</ent>⟦br⟧
